# Content Management & MDX Standards

## Content Structure
Follow the content model outlined in [prd.md](mdc:prd.md):
- `/content/about.mdx` - Personal biography and professional summary
- `/content/work/[company].mdx` - Work history with company details
- `/content/projects/[slug].mdx` - Project showcases with case studies
- `/content/skills.mdx` - Skills and technologies organized by category
- `/content/blog/[slug].mdx` - Blog posts and articles

## MDX Frontmatter Standards
Each MDX file should include proper frontmatter:
```yaml
---
title: "Page Title"
description: "Brief description for SEO"
date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
tags: [tag1, tag2]
featured: true/false
---
```

## Content Components
- Use consistent heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- Implement proper image handling with Next.js Image
- Use MDX components for interactive elements
- Maintain consistent formatting and spacing
- Include proper alt text for accessibility

## Content Organization
- Group related content by category
- Use consistent naming conventions for files
- Implement proper tagging and categorization
- Maintain content versioning and updates
- Ensure content is easily editable by non-developers

## SEO & Metadata
- Include proper meta descriptions
- Use semantic HTML structure
- Implement Open Graph and Twitter Card meta tags
- Optimize content for search engines
